&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About Vercel:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Vercel gives developers the tools and cloud infrastructure to build, scale, and secure a faster, more personalized web. As the team behind v0, Next.js, and AI SDK, Vercel helps customers like Ramp, Supreme, PayPal, and Under Armour build for the AI-native web.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Our mission is to enable the world to ship the best products. That starts with creating a place where everyone can do their best work. Whether you&#39;re building on our platform, supporting our customers, or shaping our story: You can just ship things.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the Role:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Senior Partner Marketing Manager to help build and scale co-marketing programs across Vercel’s growing partner ecosystem — from GSIs and digital agencies, to ISVs, to cloud providers like AWS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be the first dedicated hire focused on partner marketing, working cross-functionally with Sales, Field, Solutions Engineering, and Product Marketing to bring high-impact partner initiatives to life. You’ll help shape how we go to market with partners, launch new solutions, and create the stories and campaigns that drive demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who thrives in high-growth environments, enjoys building systems that scale, and wants to be at the center of product, partnerships, and pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re based within a pre-determined commuting distance of one of our offices (SF, NY), the role includes in-office anchor days on Monday, Tuesday, and Friday. If you&#39;re located beyond that distance, the role is fully remote. For location-specific details, please connect with our recruiting team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run joint marketing campaigns with top partners — with clear goals, clear assets, and clear outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Launch new integrations, marketplace listings, and co-sell motions with tight GTM plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build partner-facing content that actually gets used: case studies, one-pagers, landing pages, decks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute partner activations — digital, in-person, and everything in between&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with field teams and sales to make sure we’re covering the right accounts, not just checking boxes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain a library of stories and proof points that partners can rally around&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on campaign performance, sourced pipeline, and influence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About You:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years in B2B marketing, with 3+ years focused on partner or ecosystem marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve owned GTM campaigns with GSIs, ISVs, or cloud platforms — and know what “good” looks like&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with a bias toward shipping — you know when to workshop and when to execute&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writer and storyteller — especially when simplifying technical products for external audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative, clear communicator who works well with sales and cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: You know your way around the frontend, ecommerce, or cloud developer ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extra credit: You’ve built programs with AWS — especially marketplace or co-sell&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Benefits:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Competitive compensation package, including equity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Inclusive Healthcare Package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Learn and Grow - we provide mentorship and send you to events that help you build your network and skills.&lt;/li&gt;
